This paper focuses on analyzing the topical distribution of information produced and consumed by social media users, specifically on Twitter. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses personalized recommendations provided by Twitter, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of the content of tweets and the identification of topics can be categorized under natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also touches upon the privacy and security concerns of social media, which can be categorized under cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of news organizations on social media, which can be categorized under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
